Comments.
Additional characters to the original description (
♀
) are as follows: body [12.5] 12.0–17.0 mm; mar- gin of gena behind eyes flat in dorsal view; margin of gena [0.4] 0.6–1.0× length of eye in dorsal view; tarsal claw with basal lobe quadrangular, with claw apex slightly overtaking the posterior margin of lobe. 
Male.
(
Figs 85–86
). Similar to female in structure and coloration, except margin of gena 0.6–0.7× length of eye in dorsal view; posterior ocelli separated from eyes by 0.6× its diameter in dorsal view; sternite IX (
Fig 88
) longer than high, with lateral and anterior margins strongly sclerotised, lateral margin slightly concave and posterior margin concave, with few bristles widely spaced posteriorly. Genital capsule (
Figs 89–90
): Paramere truncated apically, slightly narrower than the parameral lamina, with bristles except in posterior margin; volsellar lamina with bristles anteroapically spaced in anterior margin and with a set of four to five bristles in anterolateral region, just below the base of the digitus; cuspis robust with about four to five teeth aligned in the mid part until apex and with three to four few bristles spaced in apical region; digitus with teeth on apex, rounded distally and angular ventrally, with the margins of the apical region narrower than base; aedeagus with few teeth on apex and its apex slightly curved downward in lateral view.
